IIUC you've configured each of systemd services to run automatically at startup, and each of them is configuring the LED group differently. Is that what you want? Should these WantedBy lines be removed?

We don't need to run any of them at startup. The current mechanism is phosphor-dbus-monitor starts at bmc bootup, monitor the event listed in the config file and execute the corresponding service upon the signal received. I took those WantedBy out.
